'''Chu Chang-kyun''' ({{Korean|주창균|朱昌均}}; November 7, 1921 – December 29, 2012) served as the President of the [[Korea Scout Association]]. In 1988, Chu was awarded the 189th ''[[Bronze Wolf]]'', the only distinction of the [[World Organization of the Scout Movement]], awarded by the World Scout Committee for exceptional services to world Scouting.
