{{Infobox book | italic title = <!--(see above)--> | name = The Misfit Economy: Lessons in Creativity From Pirates, Hackers, Gangsters, And Other Informal Entrepreneurs | image = The Misfit Economy.jpg | image_size = 200 | alt = | caption = | authors = Alexa Clay, Kyra Maya Phillips | country = USA | language = English | subjects = [[Business]], [[Entrepreneurship]], [[Economics]] | genre = [[Non-fiction]] | published = 2015 | publisher = [[Simon & Schuster]] | media_type = Print ([[hardcover]]) | pages = 248 | awards = | isbn = 978-14-5168882-5 | website = http://www.misfiteconomy.com/ }}
'''''The Misfit Economy: Lessons in Creativity From Pirates, Hackers, Gangsters, And Other Informal Entrepreneurs''''' is a 2015 book by [[Alexa Clay]] and Kyra Maya Phillips about the innovators and entrepreneurs amongst the [[Black market|underground economies]] and [[grey market]]s of the world.
==Reception== It has been reviewed by ''[[The Financial Times]]'',<ref>{{cite news |first=Emma|last=Jacobs |title=Review: The Misfit Economy, by Alexa Clay and Kyra Maya Phillips |url=http://www.ft.com/cms/s/2/2e9c56d0-f019-11e4-ab73-00144feab7de.html#axzz3rUNgxKnO |accessdate=16 November 2015 |work=The Financial Times |date=17 May 2015}}</ref> ''[[The National (Abu Dhabi)|The National]]'',<ref>{{cite news |first=Lianne|last=Gutcher |title=Business: Book review: Unique insights of the misfits |url=http://www.thenational.ae/business/the-life/book-review-unique-insights-of-the-misfits |accessdate=16 November 2015 |work=The National |date=1 September 2015}}</ref> ''[[Daily News (New York)|New York Daily News]]'',<ref>{{cite news |author=Cesar R. Bustamante, Jr |title=‘The Misfit Economy’ explores hackers, pirates and other fringe businessmen — but wastes opportunity: book review |url=http://www.nydailynews.com/entertainment/theater-arts/misfit-economy-explores-hackers-pirates-review-article-1.2279883 |accessdate=16 November 2015 |work=Daily News |date=9 July 2015}}</ref> ''[[The Dallas Morning News|Dallas News]]'',<ref>{{cite news |first=Jim|last=Pawlak |title=Business book reviews: The Misfit Economy and Insight Out |url=http://www.dallasnews.com/business/headlines/20150725-business-book-reviews-the-misfit-economy-and-insight-out.ece |accessdate=16 November 2015 |work=The Dallas Morning News |date=25 July 2015}}</ref> the ''[[Stanford Social Innovation Review]]''.<ref>{{Cite journal| author=Edward T. Walker | title=Leadership: The Insight of Outsiders | journal=Stanford Social Innovation Review | volume=13 | issue=4 | issn=1542-7099 |publisher=Stanford University |url=http://ssir.org/book_reviews/entry/the_insight_of_outsiders |accessdate=16 November 2015}}</ref> The authors were interviewed about the book in ''[[Forbes]]''.<ref>{{Cite web| first=David| last=Slocum |title=Leadership: Interview: Five Questions With Alexa Clay On Misfits And The Dark Side Of Innovation | publisher=Forbes| date=5 August 2015 |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/berlinschoolofcreativeleadership/2015/08/05/five-questions-with-alexa-clay-on-misfits-and-the-dark-side-of-innovation/ |website=www.forbes.com|accessdate=16 November 2015}}</ref>
